Things i have learned in order to work upon a repo shared to me-
 1st case - if repo is not being created then-
            Go to github and then click on create repo option and select profile and repo title and make it public or private as per our need then
            add collaborators if you wish and create it and then follow from step 2 below.

 2nd case- if we are added as collaborators in a repo then do the following steps-

1.git clone <repository-url>
Clones the GitHub repository to the local system.

2.cd <repository-name>
Moves into the project folder.

3.git status
Shows the current status of files in the repository.

4.git checkout -b <branch-name>
Creates a new branch and switches to it.

5.git branch
Displays all local branches.

6.git add .
Adds all changed files to the staging area.

7.git commit -m "commit message"
Saves the staged changes with a commit message.

8.git remote -v
Shows the connected remote GitHub repository URLs.

9.git pull origin main
Fetches and merges the latest changes from the main branch.

10.git push origin <branch-name>
Pushes the local branch changes to GitHub.

11.git push origin main
Pushes local main branch changes to GitHub.

Other commands -
12.git log
Displays commit history.

13.git diff
Shows differences between changed files and the last commit.

14.git fetch
Downloads changes from GitHub without merging them.

15.git merge <branch-name>
Merges the specified branch into the current branch.

16.git config --global user.name "Your Name"
Sets the Git username.

17.git config --global user.email "your@email.com"
Sets the Git email.
